snippet: Opposition supporters clashed with riot police officers in Faisalabad, leaving one person dead and several wounded.
abstract: Political violence erupts in Faisalabad, Pakistan, when opposition supporters clash with riot police, leaving one man dead and several wounded; protests then spread across Punjab Province at instigation of Imran Khan, who has been campaigning for ouster of Prime Min Nawaz Sharif.
lead_paragraph: Opposition supporters clashed with riot police officers in Faisalabad, leaving one person dead and several wounded.

headline.main: Political Strife Flares in Central Pakistan
